natural problem: What are the rightmost three digits of $5^{1993}$?
natural solution: We compute the powers of 5 modulo 1000: \begin{align} 5^0&\equiv1\pmod{1000}\\ 5^1&\equiv5\pmod{1000}\\ 5^2&\equiv25\pmod{1000}\\ 5^3&\equiv125\pmod{1000}\\ 5^4&\equiv625\pmod{1000}\\ 5^5&\equiv125\pmod{1000}.

\end{align} This pattern repeats every two terms starting at the 4th term. In particular, when $n>2$, and $n$ is odd,  \[5^n\equiv125\pmod{1000}.\] Therefore the rightmost digit of $5^{1993}$ is $\boxed{125}$.
